# pseudo-ui Shadow-DOM Theming

> **Loads when editing** the pseudo-ui render surface, the theming helpers,
> the settings store, or the tenant-style sync component. Authoritative
> detail: **`CLAUDE.DESIGNER-UI.md` â†’ *pseudo-ui Shadow-DOM Theming***
> and the **`forgepseudouithemingspec.md`** at the repo root.

## Mental model

Pseudo-ui (`@burgantech/pseudo-ui/react`) renders **inside a shadow root**
attached by `PseudoUiPseudoViewFrame`. The shadow root is the isolation
boundary: parent shell Tailwind / VS Code injected `!important` styles
cannot reach it, and Forge does **not** impose its own theme on the
canvas (R9 contract â€” *"Forge is a designer, not a stylist"*).

The shadow root receives a **three-layer cascade** plus the SDK's own
component CSS:

```
L1  Static MDC PrimeReact theme   (light or dark, mirrored from html.dark)
L0  Utilities                     (.p-hidden-accessible + Stepper override)
L2  Forge default token overrides (:host { --p-primary-color: ... })
L3  Tenant token override         (validated, optional)
Icons sheet                       (PrimeIcons + Material Icons class rules)
L4  pseudo-ui-react.css           (SDK adopts via renderRoot prop)
```

Each layer is a constructable `CSSStyleSheet` cached at module level and
swapped atomically via `shadow.adoptedStyleSheets = [...]`. The
implementation lives in
`packages/designer-ui/src/modules/quick-run/pseudo-ui/theme/buildSheets.ts`.

## The non-negotiable invariant

**`primeReactConfig.styleContainer` MUST be the shadow root.** PrimeReact
10 components carry their *structural* CSS (Stepper layout flex,
separator `flex: 1 1 0`, Dropdown hidden-accessible peers, `display:
flex` on icon containers, â€¦) as a `styles` string bundled in each
component's JS. The runtime `useStyle` hook reads
`context.styleContainer || document.head` and appends a `<style>`
element there.

If you drop the `styleContainer` override, those `<style>` elements
land in the parent `document.head`. Shadow tree elements **never see
them**. Static theme rules still apply (visual decoration), so the
canvas *looks* mostly right â€” but layout silently degrades:
- Stepper numbers render as rounded squares without connecting separators
- Dropdown native `<select>` peers leak through as ghost form controls
- Calendar / MultiSelect popovers position incorrectly

The bug is silent (no console error) and easy to miss in PR review.
**Do not remove `styleContainer: shadow` from `primeReactConfig` in
`PseudoUiPseudoViewFrame.tsx`.**

## Why no runtime `theme.preset`

`@primeuix/themes` (Lara / MDC presets) emit design-token CSS targeted
at `:root`. Inside a shadow tree `:root` matches nothing (CSS scoping
spec) â€” tokens would never bind, components would render fully
unstyled.

Token definitions come instead from the static MDC theme (with
`:root` rewritten to `:host, :root` by `shadowSafeThemeCss` in
`buildSheets.ts`) plus the Forge default override layer.

## Tenant CSS contract

Tenants override **only** CSS custom properties (`--p-*` and
`--font-family`). The validator lives in
`packages/designer-ui/src/modules/quick-run/pseudo-ui/theme/parseTenantCss.ts`:

- Token JSON input: `{ '--p-primary-color': '#FF6B35', ... }` â€” preferred.
- CSS string input: must be `:host { --foo: bar }` blocks; class
  selectors (`.d-card`, `.p-button`, â€¦) and standard CSS properties
  (`color`, `background`, â€¦) are silently dropped.
- Values containing `;`, `{`, or `}` are rejected as CSS-injection
  attempts (e.g. `;@import "evil.css"`).

This is a deliberate contract. SDK internal class names are not part of
the public API and may change in minor releases. Do not relax the
validator without coordinating with the SDK team.

## When adding a new pseudo-ui surface

If you build a new mount point for `<PseudoView>`:
- Use `PseudoUiPseudoViewFrame` (or copy its setup exactly).
- Adopt theme via `syncThemeLayers(shadow, { appTheme, tenant })`.
- Pass `renderRoot={shadow}` to `<PseudoView>` so the SDK adopts its
  own component CSS.
- Pass `primeReactConfig={{ styleContainer: shadow }}`.
- Do **not** add `theme.preset`.
- Do **not** wrap the shadow host with Forge-side border / padding /
  background â€” the developer's design decides its own chrome.

## File map

- `PseudoUiPseudoViewFrame.tsx` â€” shadow root attach + React mount + `styleContainer` wiring.
- `PseudoUiViewSurface.tsx` â€” chrome (skeleton, error boundary, action overlay) in parent DOM.
- `theme/forgeDefaults.ts` â€” M3 indigo light/dark token maps.
- `theme/buildSheets.ts` â€” `syncThemeLayers`, sheet caches, `shadowSafeThemeCss`.
- `theme/parseTenantCss.ts` â€” token-only validator + injection guard.
- `app/PseudoUiTenantStyleSync.tsx` â€” settings-driven tenant CSS link (light-DOM path + shadow-root helper).
- `store/useSettingsStore.ts` â€” `pseudoUiTenantTokens` settings field.
